(Campus Parking Availability Optimization Report) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. Problem Statement) Tj
T* (Students and faculty frequently lose time searching for parking inside a campus zone because) Tj
T* (they do not know which specific spots are currently open.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (2. Objective) Tj
T* (Design and implement an efficient algorithm that returns currently available parking spots) Tj
T* (inside a requested campus area with minimal query latency.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (3. Data \(Data fields used to build solution\)) Tj
T* (- spot_id: Unique identifier for a parking space \(example: N-101\)) Tj
T* (- area: Logical campus zone \(North, Central, South\)) Tj
T* (- row, col: Optional physical coordinates in lot grid) Tj
T* (- priority_score: Lower value means preferred proximity/access) Tj
T* (- occupancy_status: Derived runtime state \(occupied or free\)) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (4. Data Structures Used) Tj
T* (- Hash map \(spot_by_id\): spot_id -> ParkingSpot for O\(1\) direct lookup) Tj
T* (- Hash map of min-heaps \(available_heap_by_area\): area -> heap[\(priority_score, spot_id\)]) Tj
T* (- Hash set \(occupied\): contains currently occupied spot_id values for O\(1\) occupancy checks) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (5. Algorithm Design) Tj
T* (Initialization:) Tj
T* (- Insert all spots into area-specific min-heaps sorted by priority_score.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Operations:) Tj
T* (A\) get_available_spots\(area, k\)) Tj
T* (- Repeatedly pop from that area's heap.) Tj
T* (- Skip stale entries if spot is currently occupied.) Tj
T* (- Collect up to k valid free spots.) Tj
T* (- Push valid popped spots back \(to preserve future query correctness\).) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (B\) occupy\(spot_id\)) Tj
T* (- Add spot_id to occupied set if valid and not already occupied.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (C\) release\(spot_id\)) Tj
T* (- Remove spot_id from occupied set.) Tj
T* (- Reinsert into corresponding area heap.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (6. Optimization Techniques \(Improvements over naive approach, Space/time trade-offs\)) Tj
T* (Naive approach:) Tj
T* (- Scan every spot in area each query -> O\(n_area\)) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Optimized approach:) Tj
T* (- Priority heap per area + O\(1\) occupancy set.) Tj
T* (- Top candidate retrieval is O\(log n_area\) amortized; near O\(1\) when heap head is valid.) Tj
T* (- Query for k spots is approximately O\(k log n_area\) with lazy stale-skip handling.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
